{"parentUuid":"76e64f72-38be-4d13-a451-af409c8225d3","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"9aa4b798-edb6-4bb8-a075-e145d4d5fdb1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G2DxhLd65xJh38VWnZn6xA","type":"tool_result","content":"94\t\n95\tObjects as well. Refs are what `git-sync` plans and updates, but it also transfers the commits, trees, blobs, and tags needed for those refs to exist on the target.\n96\t\n97\t### Is it bidirectional?\n98\t\n99\tNo. `git-sync` is one-way: source remote to target remote. To go the other way you'd run a second invocation with the endpoints swapped.\n100\t\n101\t### Does it support create, update, and delete actions?\n102\t\n103\tYes. It supports creating refs, updating refs, force updates with `--force`, and deleting managed refs with `--prune`. `replicate` can overwrite target refs, but it is relay-only and more restrictive than `sync`.\n104\t\n105\t### How does it scale?\n106\t\n107\tThe scalable path streams pack data from the source directly into the target without materializing the full object graph locally. The in-memory `go-git` store is used for planning, ancestry checks, and fallback materialized pushes. In fallback mode, `git-sync` fetches objects into memory, computes what must be pushed, then encodes and sends a pack to the target.\n108\t\n109\t### How long does it take for a medium-sized repo?\n110\t\n111\tThere is no fixed runtime. It depends on repository size, pack size, network latency, provider speed, and whether relay is used. On the relay path, time is mostly source pack generation plus network transfer plus target receive time.\n112\t\n113\t### Does it support SSH?\n114\t\n115\tNo. `git-sync` supports smart HTTP/HTTPS only.\n116\t\n117\t### Is this one-time or does it run in the background?\n118\t\n119\t`git-sync` is a one-shot CLI/library operation. It does not run as a daemon or background watcher. Run it manually, from CI, cron, a worker, or another service.\n120\t\n121\t## Contributing\n122\t\n123\tSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md), [SECURITY.md](SECURITY.md), and [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n124\t"}]},"uuid":"c1d77f06-f595-4aab-9e71-a60d0d6bcce4","timestamp":"2026-04-30T09:28:35.483Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/gitsync/README.md","content":"\nObjects as well. Refs are what `git-sync` plans and updates, but it also transfers the commits, trees, blobs, and tags needed for those refs to exist on the target.\n\n### Is it bidirectional?\n\nNo. `git-sync` is one-way: source remote to target remote. To go the other way you'd run a second invocation with the endpoints swapped.\n\n### Does it support create, update, and delete actions?\n\nYes. It supports creating refs, updating refs, force updates with `--force`, and deleting managed refs with `--prune`. `replicate` can overwrite target refs, but it is relay-only and more restrictive than `sync`.\n\n### How does it scale?\n\nThe scalable path streams pack data from the source directly into the target without materializing the full object graph locally. The in-memory `go-git` store is used for planning, ancestry checks, and fallback materialized pushes. In fallback mode, `git-sync` fetches objects into memory, computes what must be pushed, then encodes and sends a pack to the target.\n\n### How long does it take for a medium-sized repo?\n\nThere is no fixed runtime. It depends on repository size, pack size, network latency, provider speed, and whether relay is used. On the relay path, time is mostly source pack generation plus network transfer plus target receive time.\n\n### Does it support SSH?\n\nNo. `git-sync` supports smart HTTP/HTTPS only.\n\n### Is this one-time or does it run in the background?\n\n`git-sync` is a one-shot CLI/library operation. It does not run as a daemon or background watcher. Run it manually, from CI, cron, a worker, or another service.\n\n## Contributing\n\nSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md), [SECURITY.md](SECURITY.md), and [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n","numLines":31,"startLine":94,"totalLines":124}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"76e64f72-38be-4d13-a451-af409c8225d3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"5b613073-e70b-48a1-b6ae-c6aaa99ec2b1","version":"2.1.121","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
